Networking Deep Dive + Traffic Analysis

# Core Concept -- How Data Moves (Critical)
When you type: ping google.com
This happens:
1. DNS converts google.com -> IP
2. Your computer sends packets
3. Packets travel across networks
4. Google responds

# Packets (Foundation)
What is a packet? - A packet is a small chunk of data sent across a network
Each packet contains:
Source IP
Destination IP
Data
*Think: Internet = millions of packets moving everywhere

# Important Protocols (Review + Apply)
HTTP -> Port 80
HTTPS -> Port 443
SSH -> Port 22
FTP -> Port 21
DNS -> Port 53

# Commands
## ping (connectivity test)
ping google.com
Shows:
packets sent
response time
## curl (request a website)
curl google.com
Shows raw HTML response
## netstat (network connections)
netstat -tulnp
Shows:
open ports
active connections
## ifconfig or ip a
ip a
Shows your IP address
